entry.content:
do you think they would announce meteor impact anime late september during the second half anni tsukisuta :00 i really feel that mi is next given the way they didnt announce any remini anime back in april!  its very suspicious... like it would definitely make sense that they didnt announce it cause mi is the longest out of the remini stories so they possibly cannot cover it in six episodes each only about ten minutes, so theyre probably needing more time to work on it or something. what are your thoughts on it!


honestly don't know, i might start having those thoughts if one of the ryuseitai seiyuus are announced to be in the half anniversary stream, since that's how they announced checkmate last year.  but i agree that it's soooo sus how there's a huge gap between the last anime and the next one... either the timing of the event content post-anime isn't right just yet, or it's because of meteor impact's length or... a mixture of the two or we're just overthinking it WHO KNOWS... THE WAIT IS SO MYSTERIOUS!!!
my thoughts are about the same as yours...!!! one extra thing on my mind is that when stella came out and it was revealed to be THE meteor impact answer for kanata (basically finally explaining so much about him and why he was like that in the past and a chance for him to be a hero), i was like &quot;oh... oh wait then this means we need an answer for chiaki's side of meteor impact right??? he's the other 5* his story is important too!!&quot;
so i started to think that it's SUUUPER likely that meteor impact anime will be connected to chiaki's center, rather than a special tour. especially since i strongly believe chiaki's next center will bring back megane chiaki, and the last time we saw megane chiaki (as a card) is in meteor impact so &quot;it makes sense trust me bro&quot;
BUT THEN!!! gourmet ended up being THE meteor impact answer for chiaki!! so now we're back to a special tour being way more likely, since the next person in line that needs his meteor impact answer is... madara!! but he was a 4* unlike the other 2 so i can't imagine it being meteor impact anime -&gt; mam event and nothing else HAHA chiaki and kanata were THE 5*s after all... so... special tour very likely...? considering there's still a lot to work out between these three, plus tetora's established connection with madara...?
still unclear but... i'm leaning towards that now ever since gourmet came out!! so that's all that's on my mind lately for meteor impact anime LMAO &quot;what is the mysterious event they'll release right after it. TELL ME NOW!!!!&quot;
(also to be clear i Still think chiaki center will be the megane chiaki comeback card. i will never let this go until proven wrong)
